Package edu.bu.pas.othello.traversal

Class Node

java.lang.Object
edu.bu.pas.othello.traversal.Node
public abstract class Node extends Object
A class that represents a vertex (e.g. Node) in the game tree. Nodes will contain the state of the game at this point in the game tree along with other bookkeeping information such as who the current player is, who the MAX player is, etc. Nodes also have information regarding where they are in the tree such a depth information and a method to produce child Nodes. Most importantly, Node objects contain utility values inside them as well as the last move made (e.g. the move made in the parent Node that led to this Node).

  • Constructor Details

    • Node

      public Node(PlayerType maxPlayerType, Game.GameView gameView, int depth)
      A constructor to build a Node object. This constructor will auto-call this.getTerminalUtility() if this Node is a terminal node (e.g. if the provided Game.GameView says that the game is over).
      Parameters:
      maxPlayerType - The PlayerType of the MAX player.
      gameView - The current state of the game.
      depth - The current depth of this Node in the tree.
